Got it — since you can only use inline styles (style=""), you can still make the link much more visible 👍

Here are the best options you can copy-paste directly:


---

✅ 1. Make it a button (best solution)

<a href="#"
   style="
     display:inline-block;
     background-color:#0969da;
     color:white;
     padding:12px 18px;
     border-radius:8px;
     text-decoration:none;
     font-weight:600;
     font-size:16px;
     margin-top:16px;
   ">
   → Open GitHub Copilot Governance Dashboard
</a>

👉 This is the biggest improvement — it becomes a clear CTA button.


---

✅ 2. Add simple hover effect (inline workaround)

Inline styles don’t support :hover, but you can fake it:

<a href="#"
   style="
     display:inline-block;
     background-color:#0969da;
     color:white;
     padding:12px 18px;
     border-radius:8px;
     text-decoration:none;
     font-weight:600;
   "
   onmouseover="this.style.backgroundColor='#054da3'"
   onmouseout="this.style.backgroundColor='#0969da'">
   → Open Dashboard
</a>


---

✅ 3. If you want something less “button-like”

<div style="
  background:#f6f8fa;
  padding:12px;
  border-left:4px solid #0969da;
  border-radius:6px;
  margin-top:16px;
">
  <a href="#"
     style="
       color:#0969da;
       font-weight:600;
       text-decoration:none;
     ">
     → Open GitHub Copilot Governance Dashboard
  </a>
</div>


---

✅ 4. Minimum change (quick fix)

If you can barely change anything:

<a href="#"
   style="
     color:#0969da;
     font-weight:bold;
     font-size:16px;
     text-decoration:underline;
   ">
   → Open GitHub Copilot Governance Dashboard
</a>


---

🔥 Recommendation

Use option #1 (button) — it’s the cleanest and most noticeable.


